node.title: Two new Covid-19 cases in Northland region
node.description: Northlanders are being encouraged to get tested for Covid-19, with two new cases confirmed in the region.
node.content:
["Northlanders are being encouraged to get tested for Covid-19 by the Ministry of Health, with two new cases confirmed in the region.", "", "
\nPhoto: 123rf.com\n
", "One case is in the Kait\u0101ia area and public health staff are trying to establish a possible link to previous cases.", "The other case was already in Whang\u0101rei, as a close contact to another known case. The cases will be included in today's national tally.", "Anyone with cold or flu symptoms, or who has been in contact with a recent case should be tested.", "A testing clinic at the Old Warehouse Building, at 11 Matthews Avenue, in Kait\u0101ia will be open until 2pm today.", "The prime minister and director-general of health have called a media conference for 11am this morning to give an update on the Covid-19 response."]
